Merryvale has, inter alia, the following registrations for the trademark BETWAY (the “Mark”):
Jurisdiction Registration no. Registration Date
EU 4832325 January 26, 2007
UK UK00904832325 January 26, 2007
Canada TMA702542 December 7, 2007
3. No person or entity is entitled to make use of the Mark, or any trademarks that are similar to the Mark, without first obtaining the written consent of our Client.
The Infringement
4. Our Client has recently come across the Infringing Domain Name and the Fraudulent Website, where its operator is unashamedly making use of the Mark while providing similar services to those offered by
our Client (the “Fraudulent Activity”). This is done in blatant violation of Section 4.5(3) of Digitalocean's Terms of Service Agreement (the “Agreement”).
5. The Fraudulent Activity is clearly meant to deceive users into entering the Fraudulent Website, under the mistaken assumption and belief that it is somehow related to our Client. Needless to say, our Client has never authorized the use of the Mark or any trademarks similar thereto by the operator of the Fraudulent Website.
6. These actions are causing our Client and the Super Group enormous damages which are impossible to assess at this point, as in addition to the trademark infringement, the operator’s actions expose our
Client to current and future claims from Internet users who might mistakenly believe that the Infringing Domain Name or the Fraudulent Website belong to or are associated in any way with our Client or the
Super Group.
Request for Assistance
7. We therefore request your swift interference in this matter by ceasing the provision of hosting services for the operator of the Fraudulent Website, in accordance with Section 12 of the Agreement, so as to
prevent further damages to our Client and bring an end to the infringement of its rights by the operator of the Fraudulent Website. You are also kindly requested to provide us with any contact information
you may have for the owner of the Fraudulent Website, so as to enable our Client to take direct action against them.
8. Please let us know should you require any further information with respect to our Client’s rights.
Your assistance in the matter is much appreciated. We look forward to hearing from you at your earliest convenience.
